---
import BaseLayout from '../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Portfolio"
  description="Three works by Alexandros Emmanouilidis - a prize-winning fantasy short story, an original fantasy world in development, and a Java board game with AI."
>

  <section class="section">
    <div class="container">

      <span class="section-label">Portfolio</span>
      <h1>Things I've made</h1>
      <p class="portfolio-intro">
        Three things - a short story that placed in competition, a fantasy world still
        under construction, and a board game built from scratch. More to come.
      </p>

      <div class="portfolio-list">

        <!-- Blind Tracks -->
        <article class="portfolio-item" id="blind-tracks">
          <div class="portfolio-item-meta">
            <span class="item-tag">Fiction</span>
            <span class="item-year">2026</span>
          </div>
          <div class="portfolio-item-body">
            <h2 class="item-title">Blind Tracks</h2>
            <p class="item-desc">
              A fantasy short story. Taren - a "Null", someone born without the ability to
              use the Dream - defies his chief's orders to search for a missing convoy member
              alone in a crimson storm. The story explores what it means to be powerless in a
              world built around power, and how that absence becomes its own kind of strength.
            </p>
            <p class="item-recognition">
              Third place, University of Cyprus Student Club Literary Competition 2026.
            </p>
            <a href="/portfolio/blind-tracks" class="btn btn--primary item-cta">Read the story</a>
          </div>
        </article>

        <hr class="divider" />

        <!-- Zeton -->
        <article class="portfolio-item" id="the-world">
          <div class="portfolio-item-meta">
            <span class="item-tag">Creative · WIP</span>
            <span class="item-year">Ongoing</span>
            <div class="portfolio-item-image">
              <img
                src="/images/zeton.jpg"
                alt="Zeton - two moons over a barren landscape"
                width="832"
                height="1248"
                loading="lazy"
              />
            </div>
          </div>
          <div class="portfolio-item-body">
            <h2 class="item-title">Zeton</h2>
            <p class="item-desc">
              An original fantasy world built from scratch - not adapted from existing fiction,
              not borrowing established settings. The mythology, geography, history, magic
              system, species, and internal logic of this world are being developed with the
              intention of writing a full novel set inside it. Blind Tracks is the first
              published piece set here.
            </p>
            <p class="item-recognition">
              What it shows: long-term creative ambition, original thinking, worldbuilding discipline.
            </p>
            <a href="/portfolio/the-world" class="btn btn--ghost item-cta">Learn more</a>
          </div>
        </article>

        <hr class="divider" />

        <!-- Gomoku -->
        <article class="portfolio-item" id="gomoku">
          <div class="portfolio-item-meta">
            <span class="item-tag">Java · Software</span>
            <span class="item-year">2026</span>
          </div>
          <div class="portfolio-item-body">
            <h2 class="item-title">Gomoku</h2>
            <p class="item-desc">
              A fully playable implementation of Gomoku - the Japanese five-in-a-row strategy
              game - built as first-year Computer Science coursework. Three play modes: Human
              vs Human, Human vs Computer, and Computer vs Computer. Includes an AI strategy,
              board rendering, and a full suite of JUnit unit tests.
            </p>
            <p class="item-recognition">
              What it shows: object-oriented design, AI logic, unit testing, clean code
              documentation. First-year coursework - included because it is complete,
              functional, and demonstrates structured thinking.
            </p>
            <a href="/portfolio/gomoku" class="btn btn--ghost item-cta">See the project</a>
          </div>
        </article>

      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

</BaseLayout>

<style>
  h1 {
    margin-top: var(--space-xs);
    margin-bottom: var(--space-md);
  }

  .portfolio-intro {
    font-size: 1.125rem;
    color: var(--color-text-muted);
    max-width: 60ch;
    margin-bottom: var(--space-2xl);
  }

  .portfolio-list {
    max-width: 800px;
  }

  .portfolio-item {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: 160px 1fr;
    gap: var(--space-xl);
    padding-bottom: var(--space-xl);
  }

  .portfolio-item-meta {
    padding-top: 0.35rem;
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: var(--space-xs);
  }

  .item-tag {
    font-size: 0.75rem;
    font-weight: 600;
    letter-spacing: 0.08em;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    color: var(--color-accent);
  }

  .item-year {
    font-size: 0.875rem;
    color: var(--color-text-muted);
  }

  .item-title {
    font-size: clamp(1.5rem, 3vw, 2rem);
    margin-bottom: var(--space-md);
    margin-top: 0;
  }

  .item-desc {
    font-size: 1rem;
    color: var(--color-text);
    max-width: 60ch;
    margin-bottom: var(--space-sm);
  }

  .item-recognition {
    font-size: 0.875rem;
    color: var(--color-text-muted);
    font-style: italic;
    margin-bottom: var(--space-md);
    max-width: 60ch;
  }

  .item-cta {
    align-self: flex-start;
  }

  .portfolio-item-image {
    margin-top: var(--space-md);
  }

  .portfolio-item-image img {
    width: 100%;
    height: auto;
    border-radius: 4px;
    display: block;
  }

  @media (max-width: 640px) {
    .portfolio-item {
      grid-template-columns: 1fr;
      gap: var(--space-sm);
    }

    .portfolio-item-meta {
      flex-direction: row;
      align-items: center;
      gap: var(--space-md);
    }

    .portfolio-item-image {
      max-width: 160px;
    }
  }
</style>
